The ALMA Project was started at CEA-Grenoble in 2015. The original developers are:

Natalio Mingo <natalio.mingo@cea.fr>
Jesús Carrete <jcarrete@gmail.com>
Bjorn Vermeersch <bjorn.vermeersch@cea.fr>

With contributions from:

Bonny Dongre <Bonny.Dongre@ruhr-uni-bochum.de>
Ankita Katre <ankitamkatre@gmail.com>
Georg Madsen <Georg.Madsen@ruhr-uni-bochum.de>
Tao Wang <tao.wang@icams.ruhr-uni-bochum.de>

Some of the ideas implemented in ALMA were taken from ShengBTE, an earlier solver of the Boltzmann transport equation. ShengBTE was developed by:

Wu Li <wu.li.phys2011@gmail.com>
Jesús Carrete <jcarrete@gmail.com>
Nebil Ayape Katcho <nebil.katcho@gmail.com>
Natalio Mingo <natalio.mingo@cea.fr>